The evidence with the title 'U.S. children in single-mother families ' says *in this brief, single-mother families are defined as families headed by a female with no spouse present — living with one or more own, never-married children  ... † Families are defined as “ poor ” if their total income is less than 100 percent of the official poverty threshold ( about $22,000 for a family of four) and “ low income” . 
